      "Data": "Greeks living abroad have family in Greece, fulfill military obligations, own property, pay taxes, vacation in Greece, and follow Greek news. They often lack voting rights in their country of residence without citizenship. Indifferent citizens do not vote.",
      "Warrant": "Citizens with strong ties to a country and an interest in its affairs should have the right to vote, especially when they lack such rights elsewhere. Apathy is self-selecting, implying engaged citizens want to vote.",
      "Backing": "The right to vote for Greeks residing abroad is constitutionally guaranteed. Many countries have facilitated voting through postal or electronic means for years. Strengthening democracy requires equality for all members of the electorate.",
