    "Claim": "The proposed legislative initiative is not moving in the right direction and endangers the interests of Greeks abroad, creating problems of constitutionality.",
    "Data": "The proposed legislation is the government's first legislative proposal. Articles 2 and 4 of Law 4648/2019 are being repealed. Insufficient consideration has been given to the views of Diaspora organizations. There's a possibility of 'reviving' interest in participating in the country's electoral process from political and population groups that do not maintain any relationship or connection with the Motherland.",
    "Warrant": "Constitutional provisions regarding voting rights of Greeks abroad require immediate execution. Equality, immediacy, universality, secrecy, obligation, and simultaneity of voting are not upheld. The conditions for exercising the right to vote from the place of temporary residence are not met. The pre-parliamentary consultation process did not adequately consider the observations and proposals of Diaspora Greeks. The possibility of manipulation of the electoral result by voters with no ties to Greece should be taken into consideration.",
    "Backing": "Reference to constitutional articles (108 par.1, 51 par. 4, 54 par. 4 of the Constitution 1975/1986/2001/2008/2019). The mentioned conditions for exercising the right to vote from the place of temporary residence include (a) a real connection with the country, (b) personal presence in a polling station, (c) time of absence from the country, (d) presence in the country for a certain time in the past. The author names some Greek Associations: the Special Permanent Committee on Hellenism of the Diaspora of the Hellenic Parliament, the World Inter-Parliamentary Union of Hellenism, the Services of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the recently re-established Council of Hellenes Abroad",
    "Qualifier": "None",
    "Rebuttal": "None"
  },
  "Extra suggestions": "The author suggests establishing a mandatory electronic voting system."
}

